04861nam a22008295i 9780813553252DE-B159720200505034922.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||200505t20122012nju    fo  d z      eng d  a97808135532527 a10.36019/97808135532522doi  a(DE-B1597)530332  a(OCoLC)784885426  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  anjucUS-NJ 4aPN1998.2b.P75 2012 7aPER0000002bisacsh04a791.430 28092222200aPretty People :bMovie Stars of the 1990s /cAnna Everett. 1aNew Brunswick, NJ : bRutgers University Press, c[2012] 4cÂ©2012  a1 online resource (288 p.) :b51 photograghs  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aStar Decades: American Culture/American00tFrontmatter -- tCONTENTS -- tAcknowledgments -- tIntroduction: Stardom in the 1990s -- t1 Arnold Schwarzenegger: Corporeal Charisma -- t2 Jodie Foster: Feminist Hero? -- t3 Denzel Washington: A Revisionist Black Masculinity -- t4 Julia Roberts: Cultural Phenomenon -- t5 Leonardo DiCaprio: King of the "World" -- t6 Antonio Banderas, Andy Garcia, and Edward James Olmos: Stardom, Masculinity, and "Latinidades" -- t7 Tom Hanks and Tom Cruise: The Box Office and "True Masculinity" -- t8 Angela Bassett and Halle Berry: African American Leading Ladies -- t9 Michael Douglas: An Ordinary Man -- t10 Pierce Brosnan: Licensed to Sell -- t11 Johnny Depp and Keanu Reeves: Hollywood and the Iconoclasts -- tIn the Wings -- tWorks Cited -- tContributors -- tIndex 0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aIn the 1990s, American civil society got upended and reordered as many social, cultural, political, and economic institutions were changed forever. Pretty People examines a wide range of Hollywood icons who reflect how stardom in that decade was transformed as the nation itself was signaling significant changes to familiar ideas about gender, race, ethnicity, age, class, sexuality, and nationality. Such actors as Denzel Washington, Andy Garcia, Halle Berry, Angela Bassett, Will Smith, Jennifer Lopez, and Antonio Banderas became bona fide movie stars who carried major films to amazing box-office success. Five of the decade's top ten films were opened by three women-Julia Roberts, Jodie Foster, and Whoopi Goldberg. "Chick flick" entered the lexicon as Leonardo DiCaprio became the "King of the World," ushering in the cult of the mega celebrity. Tom Hanks and Tom Cruise defined screen masculinity as stark contrasts between "the regular guy" and "the intense guy" while the roles of Michael Douglas exemplified the endangered "Average White Male." A fascinating composite portrait of 1990s Hollywood and its stars, this collection marks the changes to stardom and society at century's end.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 05. Mai 2020) 7aPERFORMING ARTS / General.2bisacsh1 aBlasini, Gilberto M1 aDonalson, Melvin1 aEverett, Anna, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFuchs, Cynthia1 aHaralovich, Mary Beth1 aHollinger, Karen1 aHoover, Tracey1 aMask, Mia1 aMcPherson, Tara1 aMiller, Toby1 aPalmer, R. Barton1 aPeberdy, Donna1 aPomerance, Murray1 aSerna, Laura Isabel1 aWilliams, Linda Ruth08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311068861008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066331040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780813553252423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780813553252.jpg  a978-3-11-066331-0  RUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  a978-3-11-068861-0  RUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MUAR  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  